  "riddle": "1. Track down the political region where representatives gather, shaped by the Irish Sea's embrace. How many Members of Parliament are elected to voice the concerns of this constituency?\n\n2. Ascend to the heights where this region rests above sea level. What is its elevation in meters?\n\n3. Survey the landscape to uncover how many healing establishments are nearby in this political expanse. What number will you find?\n\n4. Combine the elevation you found in clue 2 with the count of hospitals from clue 3. What is their total?\n\n5. Seek the neighboring constituency across the border, where history unfolded between 1999 and 2004. How many MEPs emerged from that time?\n\n6. Journey further west to find the height of the land in the area known for its rich industrial legacy. What elevation does this region boast?\n\n7. Nearby, a multitude of arenas exist where passions ignite under the lights of sport. How many stadiums lie in the vicinity?\n\n8. Determine the absolute difference between the elevation found in clue 6 and the stadium count from clue 7. What is the result?\n\n9. Delve deeper into the previous discovery, and unearth the sum of its distinct prime factors, stemming from clue 5. What does this sum yield?\n\n10. In the heart of America lies a historic street with tales of old. Look up the elevation of this storied avenue in Philadelphia. What height do you discover?\n\n11. What was the tally of seats won by the conservative faction during an election in the United Kingdom in 1999? \n\n12. Travel to the Emerald Isle, where a crucial electoral contest in 2004 took place. How many seats were contested for the European Parliament?\n\n13. Reflect on the previous answer regarding seats in Ireland and reveal the sum of its distinct prime factors from clue 12. What do they add up to?\n\n14. A simple conversion awaits! How many feet would you rise if you climbed a humble height of 10 meters?\n\n15. Inquire about a notable figure from Ireland—how many ch